When you send a request from angular and it is different of &quot;GET&quot;, angular sends two requests (CORS policy):

- First, it sends an Options, to check if &quot;Delete&quot; operation (or whatever) is allowed.
- If this request receives a 200 with the appropiate headers, Angular sends your Delete request.

So, you need to create two stubs in wiremock:

```
{
  &quot;request&quot; : {
    &quot;urlPattern&quot; : &quot;/api/deleteThis&quot;,
    &quot;method&quot; : &quot;OPTIONS&quot;
  },
  &quot;response&quot; : {
    &quot;status&quot; : 200,
    &quot;body&quot; : &quot;{}&quot;,
    &quot;headers&quot; : {
      &quot;Content-Type&quot;: &quot;application/json&quot;,
      &quot;Access-Control-Allow-Origin&quot; : &quot;*&quot;,
      &quot;Access-Control-Allow-Methods&quot; : &quot;*&quot;,
      &quot;Access-Control-Allow-Headers&quot;: &quot;Origin, Content-Type, X-Auth-Toke&quot;
    }
  }
}

{
  &quot;request&quot; : {
    &quot;urlPattern&quot; : &quot;/api/deleteThis&quot;,
    &quot;method&quot; : &quot;DELETE&quot;
  },
  &quot;response&quot; : {
    &quot;status&quot; : 200,
    &quot;body&quot; : &quot;{}&quot;,
