answers.body_markdown:
As expected, your code generator is at version 2.20, [which is before `@Subcomponent.Factory` was introduced in 2.22](https://github.com/google/dagger/releases/tag/dagger-2.22). This causes the annotation processor step to fail because it was written before `@Subcomponent.Factory` existed, even though in your project you can _compile_ references to it since you&#39;re including the `api` for Dagger 2.35.1. Newer versions of the annotation processor properly know to check for either a Factory _or_ a Builder.

In any case, you should never use a different version of the `annotationProcessor` lines compared to the `api` or `implementation` lines: this has caused [other difficult-to-diagnose errors](https://stackoverflow.com/a/50534908/1426891) before.

The placeholder version `2.x` [no longer seems to be available](https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/google/dagger/dagger/), so instead change all `dagger` lines to the same value (2.35.1) or the latest value (2.41 as of March 2022).

```gradle
api &#39;com.google.dagger:dagger-android:2.35.1&#39;
api &#39;com.google.dagger:dagger:2.35.1&#39;
annotationProcessor &#39;com.google.dagger:dagger-android-processor:2.35.1&#39;
annotationProcessor &#39;com.google.dagger:dagger-compiler:2.35.1&#39;
```

